# Fixing Brightness Control on Lenovo Laptops with NVIDIA GPU and Nouveau Driver (Kali Linux)
The Problem
Lenovo Legion/LOQ laptops with NVIDIA GPUs running in discrete graphics mode with the Nouveau driver have non-functional brightness controls. The brightness slider moves but the screen brightness doesn't change.
Why This Happens

Laptop is in "Discrete Graphics Only" mode (AMD iGPU disabled in BIOS)
The nvidia_wmi_ec_backlight interface is created but doesn't actually control hardware with Nouveau
Hardware brightness control requires either:

Hybrid graphics mode with AMD iGPU enabled, OR
NVIDIA proprietary drivers (not recommended due to instability)



The Solution: Software Brightness Control via xrandr
Instead of hardware backlight control, we use xrandr to adjust software brightness (dims pixels rather than backlight).

Step-by-Step Fix
1. Find Your Display Name
bashxrandr | grep " connected"
Output example: eDP-1 connected 1920x1080+0+0...
2. Test Manual Brightness Control
bashxrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 0.5   # 50%
xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 1.0   # 100%
xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 0.3   # 30%
3. Install Required Tools
bashsudo apt install zenity redshift
4. Create the Control Script
bashmkdir -p ~/.local/bin
nano ~/.local/bin/brightness-menu-zenity.sh
Paste this content:
bash#!/bin/bash

# Ultimate Display Control - Brightness + Redshift
CHOICE=$(zenity --list \
    --title="Display Control" \
    --text="Select brightness or color temperature:" \
    --column="Setting" \
    --height=500 \
    --width=350 \
    "Brightness: 10% (Very Dim)" \
    "Brightness: 30% (Dim)" \
    "Brightness: 50% (Medium)" \
    "Brightness: 70% (Bright)" \
    "Brightness: 100% (Full)" \
    "Redshift: 2500K (Ultra Warm/Night)" \
    "Redshift: 3000K (Very Warm/Late Night)" \
    "Redshift: 3500K (Warm)" \
    "Redshift: 4500K (Evening)" \
    "Redshift: 5500K (Daylight)" \
    "Redshift: 6500K (Neutral/Off)" \
    "Reset Everything (100% + Neutral)")

case "$CHOICE" in
    "Brightness: 10% (Very Dim)")
        xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 0.1
        zenity --info --text="Brightness set to 10%" --timeout=1 --width=200
        ;;
    "Brightness: 30% (Dim)")
        xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 0.3
        zenity --info --text="Brightness set to 30%" --timeout=1 --width=200
        ;;
    "Brightness: 50% (Medium)")
        xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 0.5
        zenity --info --text="Brightness set to 50%" --timeout=1 --width=200
        ;;
    "Brightness: 70% (Bright)")
        xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 0.7
        zenity --info --text="Brightness set to 70%" --timeout=1 --width=200
        ;;
    "Brightness: 100% (Full)")
        xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 1.0
        zenity --info --text="Brightness set to 100%" --timeout=1 --width=200
        ;;
    "Redshift: 2500K (Ultra Warm/Night)")
        redshift -O 2500
        zenity --info --text="Color Temp set to 2500K (Ultra Warm)" --timeout=1 --width=250
        ;;
    "Redshift: 3000K (Very Warm/Late Night)")
        redshift -O 3000
        zenity --info --text="Color Temp set to 3000K (Very Warm)" --timeout=1 --width=250
        ;;
    "Redshift: 3500K (Warm)")
        redshift -O 3500
        zenity --info --text="Color Temp set to 3500K (Warm)" --timeout=1 --width=250
        ;;
    "Redshift: 4500K (Evening)")
        redshift -O 4500
        zenity --info --text="Color Temp set to 4500K (Evening)" --timeout=1 --width=250
        ;;
    "Redshift: 5500K (Daylight)")
        redshift -O 5500
        zenity --info --text="Color Temp set to 5500K (Daylight)" --timeout=1 --width=250
        ;;
    "Redshift: 6500K (Neutral/Off)")
        redshift -x
        zenity --info --text="Color Temp set to 6500K (Neutral)" --timeout=1 --width=250
        ;;
    "Reset Everything (100% + Neutral)")
        xrandr --output eDP-1 --brightness 1.0
        redshift -x
        zenity --info --text="Everything Reset!\nBrightness: 100%\nColor: Neutral" --timeout=2 --width=250
        ;;
esac
Important: Replace eDP-1 with your actual display name from step 1.
Make it executable:
bashchmod +x ~/.local/bin/brightness-menu-zenity.sh
5. Test the Script
bash~/.local/bin/brightness-menu-zenity.sh
6. Create Desktop Launcher
bashmkdir -p ~/.local/share/applications
nano ~/.local/share/applications/brightness-control.desktop
